FT  01 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Blackwood Hodge Pounds 17.9m in red and
ceasing payouts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BLACKWOOD HODGE, the international distributor of earth-moving equipment
taken over last autumn by BM Group, reported a pre-tax loss of Pounds 17.9m
for the six months ended last December compared with a profit of Pounds
11.4m a year earlier.
It said it would cease paying dividends on preferred or ordinary shares
because difficult trading conditions were likely to result in a 'substantial
deficit of distributable reserves' for the period to end-June.
Turnover fell from Pounds 240.1m to Pounds 181.7m, reflecting disposals and
other actions initiated by BM. Restructuring costs and the write-down of
assets resulted in an extraordinary loss of Pounds 13.9m. The net loss after
the charge and the last preference share dividends totalling Pounds 725,000
was Pounds 34.9m (12.74p per share) against a profit of Pounds 6m (5.09p)
before.
The company will continue to report results because its preference shares
remain outstanding but it has changed its fiscal year-end to June 30 to
match BM's.
