FT  01 MAY 91 / Letter: Coincidences
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr JONOTHAN SULTAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Isn't it rather ironic that on Monday, the Bank of England launched an
initiative, spearheaded by Mr Robin Leigh-Pemberton, to identify areas of
legal uncertainty that might harm London's standing as an international
financial centre?
Is this the same Mr Robin Leigh-Pemberton who refuses to answer
Parliamentary questions under oath regarding the Harrods takeover by the
Al-Fayed brothers? It must be an uncanny coincidence.
May I suggest that one of the Al-Fayeds spearheads the campaign, as this
might attach more weight to it]
Jonothan Sultan,
75 Leicester Street,
Wolverhampton,
West Midlands
