<HEADLINE>
FT  01 MAY 91 / Business school to probe competitiveness of City
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW ADONIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE London Business School is to conduct a wide-ranging independent
investigation into the competitiveness of the City of London, it was
announced yesterday.
Funding of Pounds 1.5m for the City Research Project is being provided by
the Corporation of London, the local authority for the City. Professor
Richard Brealey, Professor of Corporate Finance at the LBS, will be project
director.
The investigation is expected to take three years. Its purpose is to
identify and, where possible, to quantify the elements making up the City's
competitive position. They will be compared with those of other financial
centres - particularly New York, Tokyo, Paris and Frankfurt.
The corporation's initiative follows consultations with the Bank of England
and the Department of Trade and Industry.
Professor Brealey said yesterday that the main thrust of the research
programme would be identification of 'the key determinants of
competitiveness and how these are shifting over time'.
</TEXT>
