<TEXT>
Algeria yesterday offered to submit its nuclear programme to international
inspection following a series of western newspaper allegations that it had
embarked, with China, on a secret project to develop atomic weapons, Francis
Ghiles writes.
Ministry of Scientific Research officials in Algiers told the El Moudjahid
newspaper: 'Now is the time to supply international public opinion with
information concerning the peaceful use of nuclear energy'. The nuclear
programme is being developed in Ouessera, near the town of Bouira 80km from
Algiers.
