FT  30 APR 91 / International Company News: Polish group still confident
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BOBINSKI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
UNIVERSAL, a Polish foreign trade company privatised last year, has reported
an after-tax profit of 205.9bn zlotys (Dollars 22m) for 1990, of which 58
per cent is to be paid to shareholders as a dividend of 8,000 zlotys per
share, writes Christopher Bobinski in Warsaw.
When the company was privatised last summer the share price was 20,000
zlotys. The current price is 38,200.
The company plans to spend 115bn zlotys on state food processing plants, a
metal works and on property and retail trade investments. Mr Dariusz
Przywieczerski, managing director, said he was 'confident' about this year's
results.
</TEXT>
