<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 91 / International Company News: PepsiCo in 13% climb
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PEPSICO, the world's second biggest soft drinks company, yesterday turned in
a 13 per cent rise in first-quarter net earnings with strong growth in its
soft drinks and restaurants businesses offsetting lower results from snack
foods operations.
The figures were in line with expectations and shares in PepsiCo fell
Dollars 1 7/8 to Dollars 30 1/4 at yesterday's close.
For the three months to March 23, PepsiCo recorded net income of Dollars
205.4m or 26 cents a share, against Dollars 181.9m or 23 cents a year
earlier. Sales advanced 12 per cent to Dollars 4.12bn. Pre-tax profits in
the first three months of 1991 rose 15 per cent to Dollars 316m.
PepsiCo's soft drinks business suffered from the loss of the Burger King
account and volume fell 1 per cent. Sales , however, rose 7 per cent to
Dollars 1.4bn and operating profits increased 8 per cent to Dollars 161.1m.
Operating profits from PepsiCo's international soft drinks business surged
45 per cent to Dollars 17.7m on sales which climbed 35 per cent to Dollars
344.6m.
</TEXT>
