<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 91 / Unit trust accounting rules
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ACCOUNTING and disclosure rules for unit trusts were published yesterday by
the Investment Management Regulatory Organisation (Imro). The rules, in the
form of a statement of recommended practice, have the backing of the
regulatory body and so are binding on unit trusts.
They are based on current best practice in the industry and should make
little difference to most unit trusts, Imro said.
Among the more important rules is a tighter definition of when expenses can
be treated as capital rather than revenue items. The regulations are
intended to standardise reporting across the industry, which will make
comparison between unit trusts easier.
</TEXT>
