FT  30 APR 91 / Jury hears of secret tape
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A US CUSTOMS undercover agent explained at the Old Bailey yesterday how he
secretly tape-recorded a meeting between British-based executives and Iraqis
during an alleged plot to export nuclear detonating devices to Iraq.
Mr Daniel Supnick posed as Mr Dan Saunders, export manager of CSI, the US
manufacturer that made electrical capacitors allegedly wanted by the Iraqis.
