</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SOUTH Africa is to raise R2bn (Pounds 455.6m) by reducing strategic
stockpiles of oil built up as a result of the international oil embargo, and
will spend the money on development programmes including projects aimed at
ending township violence, President F W de Klerk said yesterday.
