AXA, the French insurance group, has reported a 23 per cent rise in net
profits last yearto FFr3.35bn (Dollars 560m)
The group, including the former Compagnie du Midi but not the Normandy
mutual companies which are its ultimate owners, said insurance premium
income rose by 8 per cent to FFr39.4bn, with gross revenue from banking and
