<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 91 / German Green party conference does not support 'realo'
takeover
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite an incident when a delegate aimed a water pistol at another member
of Germany's Green party the Greens took steps towards creating a more
conventional party structure at their weekend conference. However, they did
not, as had been expected, support a full-scale takeover by the pragmatic
'realo' wing.
The conference abolished the rotation principle, under which representatives
served only one term in office, and which had helped to mark the Greens as a
counter-culture movement rather than a real party. Also, a group of far-left
ecologists decided to leave the Greens. However the Greens stopped short of
swallowing all the 'realo' medicine and elected two left-wing leaders.
